Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity of .alpha.-Na2NpO4 has been measured for the first time in the temperature range 2.1-301 K using a Quantum Design PPMS (Physical Property Measurement System) calorimeter. The heat capacity and entropy values at 298.15 K have been derived as Cop,m(.alpha.-Na2NpO4, cr, 298.15 K) = (151.9 +- 4.6) J K-1mol-1and Som(.alpha.-Na2NpO4, cr, 298.15 K) = (178.3 +- 4.3) J K-1mol-1, respectively. The standard entropy of .alpha.-Na2NpO4 follows the trend shown by the isostructural compound .alpha.-Na2UO4 and the alkaline earth uranates MgUO4, SrUO4, BaUO4, and Cs2UO4. When combined with the entropies of the constituent elements, these data yield a standard entropy of formation at 298.15 K as DSom(.alpha.-Na2NpO4, cr, 298.15 K) = - (385.1 +- 4.3) J K-1mol-1. Using the enthalpy of formation tabulated in the literature, the standard Gibbs energy of formation was calculated at 298.15 K as DGom(.alpha.-Na2NpO4,cr, 298.15 K) =(-1649.0 +- 5.8) kJ mol-1.
